					*****************************
                    *         DTNPERF 3         *
                    *                           *
                    * installation instructions *
                    *****************************
                    
         ---------------        COMPILE         ---------------

Before compilng dtnperf make sure that the library bp_abstraction_layer
is compiled and optionally installed in /usr/lib

To compile the dtnperf application use the script compile.sh.
If you have installed libbp_abstraction_layer.so in /usr/lib, 
you have only to indicate as parameter of the script the dir 
of bp_abstraction_layer sources. This is necessary to let the 
compiler to find the headers of the library.

Eg: 
$ sh compile.sh /home/bp-abstraction-layer/bp_abstraction_layer/src 

If you have not installed the library because you are not the
administrator of the system, you can indicate as second parameter
the dir of the file libbp_abstraction_layer.a.
So the compiler will create a static executable.

Eg: 
$ sh compile.sh /home/bp-abstraction-layer/bp_abstraction_layer/src
			/home/bp-abstraction-layer/bp_abstraction_layer/
			
Anyway, the script contains a simple gcc command, you can modify 
it.

         ---------------         INSTALL        ---------------

To install simply copy the file dtnperf in /usr/bin

Eg:
# install dtnperf -m 755 /usr/bin/


NOTE:
This is a temporary compiling solution, it will be provided a better 
way to compile the source using configure and make.


